shared_text:
Massachusetts Science Teachers Association
December 13, 2019 at 9:35 AM ¬∑

Congratulations to our 2019 Joann Blum Inspiration in Environmental Education Award winner: Second grade teacher, Catherine Starsiak of William Sheehan Elementary School in Westwood, Massachusetts . In 2019 Catherine inspired and helped her 2nd graders start a compost initiative by presenting to and convincing the administration to bring composting to the Westwood (MA) Public Schools during lunch. Catherine shows students that they can have a positive impact on their environment, displaying the beauty that comes from one person's commitment to nature. Catherine is helping to grow students who value the environment they live in and this will have a lasting impact on the #WestwoodMA community and beyond. Thank you, Catherine! #MAScienceTeachers

post_text: Reminder: The School Committee is holding its second set of School Building Project Community Forums this Monday, December 9, and Thursday, December 12, both at 7 pm in the Thurston Middle School cafeteria. These forums will focus almost entirely on next generation educational practices that will play a crucial role in the design of the new school. You will hear about current best practices and research in child development, teaching, and learning, and will then be able to participate in an educational visioning activity that will help inform our design team's work. Please join us to provide your input on our children's educational programming! Both Community Forums will have similar formats, so feel free to attend either session.

post_text:
Thurston Middle School presents Myths at the Edge of the World by Matt Webster.

Four campers are not only lost in the woods, they are lost at the edge of the world with no land, water, stars or sun. The only way to bring life back is to ask the right questions of the wind. This play takes a closer look at myths about the nature from around the world. This play features a talented cast and crew from Thurston Middle School's sixth grade class.

Performances are Friday November 16th at 7pm and Saturday November 17th at 2pm. Tickets are $10 for adults and $7 for students and senior citizens. Tickets may be purchased at the door or online at https://myths.brownpapertickets.com/
